@startuml
!theme plain
title AAS-CIM Integration Workflow

actor "Client" as User
box "Integration Layer" #AliceBlue
    participant "Integration API" as IntAPI
end box

box "AAS Generator Service" #LightGreen
    participant "Generator API" as GenAPI
    participant "AAS Creator" as Creator
    participant "AAS-CIM Linker" as LinkerAAS
    participant "CIM-AAS Linker" as LinkerCIM
    participant "RabbitMQ Consumer" as Consumer
end box

box "Message Broker" #Orange
    queue "RabbitMQ" as MQ
end box

box "Persistent Storage (Docker Volumes)" #LightGrey
    database "File System" as FS
end box

box "BaSyx Environment" #LightBlue
    participant "AAS Environment" as BaSyxEnv
    participant "AAS Registry" as BaSyxReg
end box

autonumber "<b>[0]"

== 1. Workflow Initiation ==
User -> IntAPI: POST /run\n{"workflow": "full", "equipment": "..."}
IntAPI -> GenAPI: POST /api/generate-aas
activate GenAPI

== 2. Step 1: AAS Creation ==
GenAPI -> Creator: process_single_csv(emit_event=true)
activate Creator
Creator -> FS: Read equipment CSV from /app/assets
Creator -> FS: Read Modbus mapping CSV from /app/asset_modbus_mapping
Creator -> Creator: Generate AAS & Submodels JSON
Creator -> FS: **Write** AAS JSON to /app/basyx_aas
Creator -> MQ: Publish event ("aasx.created")
deactivate Creator
GenAPI --> IntAPI: 200 OK (Sync) or 202 Accepted (Async)
IntAPI --> User: 200 OK / 202 Accepted

== 3. Step 2: Link AAS to CIM (Event-Driven) ==
MQ -> Consumer: Deliver message ("aasx.created")
activate Consumer
Consumer -> LinkerAAS: link_aas_to_cim(payload, emit_event=true)
activate LinkerAAS
LinkerAAS -> FS: Read AAS JSON from /app/basyx_aas
LinkerAAS -> FS: Read CIM EQ XML from /app/Grids/CIM3
LinkerAAS -> LinkerAAS: Add "CimProperties" Submodel
LinkerAAS -> FS: **Update** AAS JSON in /app/basyx_aas
LinkerAAS -> MQ: Publish event ("aasx.linked_to_cim")
deactivate LinkerAAS
Consumer -> MQ: ACK message
deactivate Consumer

== 4. Step 3: Link CIM to AAS (Event-Driven) ==
MQ -> Consumer: Deliver message ("aasx.linked_to_cim")
activate Consumer
Consumer -> LinkerCIM: link_cim_to_aas(payload, emit_event=true)
activate LinkerCIM
LinkerCIM -> FS: Read CIM EQ XML from /app/Grids/CIM3
LinkerCIM -> LinkerCIM: Add <aasReference> to CIM element
LinkerCIM -> FS: **Update** CIM EQ XML in /app/Grids/CIM3
LinkerCIM -> MQ: Publish event ("cim.linked_to_aas")
deactivate LinkerCIM
Consumer -> MQ: ACK message
deactivate Consumer

== 5. Step 4: BaSyx Registration (Triggered by API) ==
note right of GenAPI: The final registration is handled\nby the synchronous API call's logic\nafter all linking is complete.
GenAPI -> FS: Read final AAS JSON from /app/basyx_aas
GenAPI -> BaSyxEnv: POST /shells (Register AAS)
GenAPI -> BaSyxEnv: POST /submodels (Register Submodels)
GenAPI -> BaSyxReg: POST /shell-descriptors (Register Endpoint)
deactivate GenAPI

@enduml

